The paper deals with the problem of computing the minimum vertex cover on hypergraphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of LP relaxation and integrality gap analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The analysis of Long Codes and cross-intersecting collections of set families suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT).
